      <abstract>
        <p>Special May 7 issue prompts spirited debate about realiability of polls and reader response to photo essay on psychiatrists' offices</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Our special issue ''The Way We Live Now'' prompted a spirited debate about the reliability of polls. Readers were also fascinated by the photo essay on psychiatrists' offices, which inspired some to analyze everything from the couches to the clutter to the placement of the boxes of tissues.</p>
      </block>
